==Description== <!--T:2-->

<!--T:3-->
[[Image:BIM box screenshot.png|1024px]]

<!--T:4-->
The '''BIM Box''' tool allows you to create a standard [[Part_Box|Part Box]], but instead of creating the object and letting you specify its dimensions and position afterwards, like the original [[Part_Workbench|Part Workbench]] tool does, this tool allows you to place and define the box dimensions graphically when creating the object. Boxes are basic [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuboid cuboid] shapes, that can be used as a base of any other kind of BIM object later on.

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Press the {{KEY|[[Image:BIM_Box.svg|16px]] [[BIM_Box|Box]]}} button
# Click a first point to define a first corner of the box. It can be any of the box corners
# Click a second point to define a first edge of the box, starting from the first point
# Click a third point to define a first face of the box, orthogonal to the first edge
# Click a fourth point to define the extrusion distance of the first face, forming the final box


